"title": "4029: world, human beings in",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4029",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The world is intended to be the dwelling-place of humanity, as the height of God's creation. Human beings are organised within the world into groupings and nations and have a God-given authority to rule.</p>\n<h2>The responsibility of human beings to rule</h2>\n<h3>Over the earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:15-Gen2:16\">GEN 2:15–2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:25-Gen1:26\">GEN 1:25–1:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:29\">GEN 1:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:4-Ps8:6\">PSA 8:4–8:6</a></p>\n<h3>Over the animal kingdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:28\">GEN 1:28</a></strong> <em>“subdue” and “rule” do not give liberty to exploit and abuse but responsibility for caring for and bringing the best out of God's world.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:1-Gen9:5\">GEN 9:1–9:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:6-Deut22:7\">DEU 22:6–22:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:23-Prov27:27\">PRO 27:23–27:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:25-Matt6:26\">MAT 6:25–6:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:11-Acts10:13\">ACT 10:11–10:13</a></p>\n<h2>The response of human beings to God's commission to rule</h2>\n<h3>Failure through abuse</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:2-Hos4:3\">HOS 4:2–4:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:12\">GEN 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:11-Gen6:12\">GEN 6:11–6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:15-Deut28:21\">DEU 28:15–28:21</a></p>\n<h3>Refusal to fill the earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:5-Gen11:7\">GEN 11:5–11:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:17\">GEN 4:17</a></p>\n<h3>Obedience and blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:4-Deut28:5\">DEU 28:4–28:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:25\">GEN 49:25</a></p>\n<h2>The ordering of nations within the world</h2>\n<h3>By language</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:8-Gen11:9\">GEN 11:8–11:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen10:5\">GEN 10:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:24\">NEH 13:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:22\">EST 1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:6-Acts2:8\">ACT 2:6–2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:6\">REV 14:6</a></p>\n<h3>By race</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:9\">REV 7:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9\">REV 5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:7\">REV 13:7</a></p>\n<h3>By territory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:26\">ACT 17:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:11-Gen13:12\">GEN 13:11–13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:27-Num13:29\">NUM 13:27–13:29</a></p>\n<h3>By their rise and fall</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:7-Jer18:10\">JER 18:7–18:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:6\">2CH 15:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:2\">ISA 19:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:10\">JER 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:17-Dan7:18\">DAN 7:17–7:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:7\">MAT 24:7</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:8\">MRK 13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:10-Luke21:11\">LUK 21:10–21:11</a></p>\n<h3>By government</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1\">ROM 13:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:21\">DAN 2:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:17\">DAN 4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13-1Pet2:14\">1PE 2:13–2:14</a></p>\n<h2>The world as the object of the gospel proclamation</h2>\n<h3>God sent Jesus Christ to this world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16\">JHN 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:22\">ISA 45:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:10\">JHN 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:29\">JHN 1:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:2\">1JN 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:9\">1JN 4:9</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are commanded to evangelise this world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18-Matt28:19\">MAT 28:18–28:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:15\">MRK 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:46-Luke24:47\">LUK 24:46–24:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a></p>",
